Asus has revealed its Strix GD30 gaming desktop, sporting a black-and-white design with interchangeable front panels. The PC boasts the latest in high-end gaming hardware, including an Nvidia GeForce GTX 1080 graphics card and Intel 7th-generation Core i7 processor. The ATX chassis uses an advanced thermal system to cool the hardware, and includes an isolated chamber for the system’s power supply. A built-in hanger allows gamers to mount their headphones on the case when not in use, and the desktop features Aura RGB lighting. Release date and pricing information for the Asus Strix GD30 is not yet available.   